<HEADLINE>
FT  15 SEP 94 / Observer: Downpour
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
It would seem sensible for companies to choose appropriate muzak to pipe
over their telephone line to entertain or otherwise those callers left on
hold. Walt Disney pumps out theme music from its films. British Airways
trills arias from its television commercials. But the prize for the most
apposite piece of music must surely go to the embattled French bank, Credit
Lyonnais. Its current choice is Gene Kelly's classic, Singing in the Rain.
</TEXT>
