<HEADLINE>
FT  14 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Norweb re-purchase
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Norweb yesterday became the sixth regional electricity group to re-purchase
its own shares by buying back 5m of its own shares representing 2.89 per
cent of its issued capital, at 795p a share.
Meanwhile South Western Electricity bought back a further 500,000 of its
shares at 766p bringing the total shares it has repurchased in recent weeks
to 4.75m shares representing about 3.9 per cent of its capital.
