<HEADLINE>
FT  14 SEP 94 / UK Company News: Boyd leaves Goal Petrol
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PEGGY HOLLINGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Goal Petroleum, the oil and gas explorer, is likely to look beyond the North
Sea for growth now that Mr David Boyd is retiring after 20 years as managing
director.
Mr Boyd's retirement was announced yesterday, along with interim results
showing a 36 per cent fall in net profits from Pounds 2.77m to Pounds 1.76m
for the six months to June 30.
The profits were hit by the sharp fall in oil prices over the last 12
months. Turnover was down from Pounds 20.9m to Pounds 20.1m although
production rose by 23 per cent to 12,300 barrels of oil equivalent a day.
Mr Boyd, 59, is closely identified with Goal, where he has worked since
shortly after its flotation in 1973. He will be replaced by Mr Duncan
Ritchie, the commercial director.
Earnings per share fell by 37 per cent from 2.07p to 1.31p.
</TEXT>
