FT  14 SEP 94 / Pounds 2.16bn capital issues in August
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
New capital issues worth Pounds 2.16bn were announced by the financial and
corporate sector last month, with a total of Pounds 851m denominated in
sterling, Bank of England figures showed yesterday.
Gross issues by UK borrowers totalled Pounds 2.52m, the Bank said. After
redemption net issues totalled Pounds 1.59bn.
The largest issue announced was Dollars 999m for Aircraft Lease Portfolio
Securitisation in nine tranches of fixed-rate bonds and floating-rate notes.
The biggest share issue was the last instalment for Pounds 200m for
Kleinwort European Privatisation Investment Trust.
Halifax Building Society and HMC Mortgage Notes 12 announced floating-rate
notes of Dollars 500m and Pounds 210m respectively and fixed-rate bond
issues were made by British Telecom Finance for Pounds 300m and Dollars
375m, and by Halifax Building Society and European Investment Bank for
Pounds 200m each.
