winter, but ruled out further 'bloody upheavals'.
Speaking on German television, he voiced concern about future unemployment
and food supplies, but did not predict a repeat of last October's armed
rebellion. 'We have extremists who think their purpose in life is to
demonstrate and shout in the city squares,' Mr Chernomyrdin said, but
